  "title": "Architecture Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>•\tMinimum 3 years’ experience in renovation / construction projects</p><p>•\tDiploma or Degree in Civil Engineering / Architecture / Construction-related field</p><p>•\tAble to coordinate with all sub-contractors (ID, M&E, carpentry, tiling, electrical, plumbing, etc.)</p><p>•\tStrong in planning, scheduling, and site coordination</p><p>•\tExperience in document submission (drawings, permits, progress reports, authorities / consultants)</p><p>•\tFamiliar with renovation workflows and site operations</p><p>•\tGood communication and problem-solving skills</p><p>•\tAble to work independently and manage multiple projects</p><p></p><p>Job Responsibilities:</p><p>•\tCoordinate renovation works with all sub-contractors</p><p>•\tPrepare and manage project schedules and work plans</p><p>•\tEnsure works follow drawings, timeline, and quality standards</p><p>•\tHandle submission of drawings, documents, and reports</p><p>•\tLiaise with owners, designers, consultants, and site teams</p><p>•\tAttend site meetings and resolve on-site issues</p><p>•\tTrack progress and update management regularly</p>",
